"},"burialDate":"+1175","burialPlace":{"address":"Church of Saint John Baptist, Pitney, South Somerset district, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"Walter Reynell\nPLEASE STOP JUST CUTTING AND PASTING...THIS MAN WAS BORN IN 1846 AND MARRIED EMILY BAKEWELL IN 1877 - IN AUSTRALIA! - https://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/reynell-walter-4917\nHis Father is a known historical Person in Australia - John Reynell (1809-1873), pastoralist and vigneron, was born on 9 February 1809 at Ilfracombe, Devon, England, son of Henry Reynell and his wife Lydia, née Fagg. His son Walter (1846-1919) was born on 27 March 1846 at Reynella Farm. Educated at the Collegiate School of St Peter, he helped his father develop the vineyards. At 21 he spent two years on Beltana station working for (Sir) Thomas Elder. He was later part-owner of Tolarno station on the Darling, and for many years ran a land agency business in Adelaide. On 16 May 1877 at Adelaide, he married EMILY BAKEWELL , daughter of William Bakewell, a lawyer of Payneham. In 1883 he became manager of Elder Smith & Co., supervising the stock business of the firm and its numerous branches.\n\nNON OF THE INFORMATION BELOW IS CORRECT!\nBirth 1104Died 1175 Immediate Family:\t\nSon of Theobald Reynell and Unknown Reynell\nHusband of Emily Reynell; Father of Captain Carew Reynell\n----\nWhere did you find that his father is Theobald? I found Walter Reynell - 1080-?  no known mother\n\n\n\n","sourceList":[{"title":"Smith Family Tree - Walter Reynell 1080","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://www.smithfamilytree.net/html/walter_reynell_1216.html","sourceUri":"397F-CGT"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1104","date":"1104","place":"Pitney, South Somerset, Somerset, England, United Kingdom"},{"name":"Christening","sources":"0","year":"1104","date":"1104","place":"Church of Saint John Baptist, Pitney, South Somerset district, Somerset, England, United Kingdom"},{"name":"Death of P