ery popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705185,"age":2,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Walter Reynell III was born in 1104, his father, Walter de Reynell II, was 25 and his mother, Elizabeth Joseph, was 24. He married Emily Bakewell. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1175, in Pitney, Somerset, England, at the age of 71."},"et":{"1104–1175":"1104–1175","1100–1136":"1100–1136","1125–1190":"1125–1190","1080–1104":"1080–1104","1080–Female":"1080–Surnud","1080":"1080","1190":"1190","Aft 1104":"pärast 1104","1106":"1106","1104":"1104","1125":"1125","1136":"1136","1100":"1100","1175":"1175","Abt 1125":"umbes 1125","Pitney, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Pitney, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Pitney, Somerset, England":"Pitney, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"1104–1175":"1104–1175","1100–1136":"1100–1136","1125–1190":"1125–1190","1080–1104":"1080–1104","1080–Female":"1080–Kuollut","1080":"1080","1190":"1190","Aft 1104":"1104 jälkeen","1106":"1106","1104":"1104","1125":"1125","1136":"1136","1100":"1100","1175":"1175","Abt 1125":"noin 1125","Pitney, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Pitney, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Pitney, Somerset, England":"Pitney, Somerset, England"},"fr":{"1104–1175":"1104–1175","1100–1136":"1100–1136","1125–1190":"1125–1190","1080–1104":"1080–1104","1080–Female":"1080–Décédée","1080":"1080","1190":"1190","Aft 1104":"après 1104","1106":"1106","1104":"1104","1125":"1125","1136":"1136","1100":"11